In case of a merger, acquisition, bankruptcy, or liquidation of our Company where the transfer of personal information may be involved, we will require new companies and/or organizations that come into possession of your personal information to continue to be bound by this Privacy Policy. If the new company or organization wishes to change its practices with respect to the collection and processing of your personal information and as outlined in this Privacy Policy, such new company or organization will ask for your consent before doing so.
We do not sell or share personal information for commercial purposes.
5. Where Your Personal Information Is Held
For users based outside of China, we store your personal information on servers on servers primarily located in the United States and Spain. The data protection and other laws of United States and Spain and/or other countries might not be as comprehensive as those in your country. By submitting your data and/or using our Services, you acknowledge that your data might be transferred, stored and processed in and to United States and Spain and other countries where we may choose to store data. In addition, when we disclose to your information to third parties, we implement appropriate safeguards to ensure that such protection is maintained and is not undermined as a result of that disclosure.
For users based in China, we store your personal information only on servers located in China. We will not process, store, share and disclose your personal information in cross-border business, or transmit your personal information abroad except as otherwise described in this Privacy Policy.
From time to time, and in accordance with the terms of this Privacy Policy and applicable privacy laws, we may transfer personal information to a recipient located outside of the jurisdiction in which you are located.
Some regions we operate in have specific laws relating to the transfer of personal information outside of the region. If you are a user located in one of such regions, before we transfer your personal information outside of the region in which you are located, we implement certain measures required by the laws of your jurisdiction.
User Location
Before We Transfer Your Personal Information
European Union
We ensure the personal information transfer complies with the GDPR and all personal information will be secure. In the event it is necessary for us to share your personal information outside of the EEA, and the recipient of such personal information is in a country that has not been deemed to offer an adequate level of data protection by the European Commission (
here
), we use standard data protection contract clauses approved by the European Commission, which require the recipient of personal information to comply with various applicable elements of GDPR. If you would like further information,
please contact us here
.
China
We will ensure that your personal information is protected at the same level as that in China in accordance with the provisions of relevant laws and regulations. In the event it is necessary for us to share the personal information of users in China with a recipient outside of China, we will ask for your consent, and inform you of the type and purpose of processing, third party recipient, security measures in place to protect such information, and the security risks of outbound transfers of your personal information. We will also perform any required obligations in accordance with the requirements of laws and regulations in China. We use a standard data protection contract approved by the Cyberspace Administration of China, which requires the recipient of personal information to comply with various applicable elements of PIPL. If you would like further information, please
contact us here
.
6. How Long Your Personal Information Is Kept
Typically, we will keep your personal information while you have an account with us or while we are providing Services to you. Thereafter, we will keep your personal information for as long as is necessary to respond to your questions, complaints, claims or as required by law, or, with regard to personal information that you share which is connected to lessons created by you and used by other users, for as long as is necessary to respond to other users’ questions, complaints, or claims with regard to such lessons. We will not retain your personal information for longer than necessary for the purposes set out in this policy. When it is no longer necessary to retain your personal information, we will delete and/or anonymize it. In the event the jurisdiction in which you are located has personal information retention legal requirements that differ with those listed in this Privacy Policy, the rules and regulations of such jurisdiction with respect to personal information retention shall control. Generally, different retention periods apply for different types of personal information as follows:
Category of Personal Information
Our Retention Period or Practice
Identifiers
For so long as your account is active or within 30 days of account deletion request / we are required by law
Commercial Information
For so long as we are required by law
Biometric Information
For so long as your account is active or within 30 days of account deletion request / we are required by law
Internet or Other Network Activity
For so long as we are required by law
Professional or Employment Information
For so long as your account is active or within 30 days of account deletion request / we are required by law
Sensitive Personal Information
For so long as your account is active or within 30 days of account deletion request / we are required by law
Inferences drawn from Personal Information
For so long as your account is active or within 30 days of account deletion request / we are required by law
User-Generated Profiles and Content
For so long as we are required by law
